<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-08-01T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-08-01T18:00:00-05:00" n="442" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d442">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">891.51A/8–144: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Chargé in Iran</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Ford</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-08-01T19:00:00-04:00">August
                                        1, 1944—7 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>464. Ambassador Morris<note n="26" xml:id="d442fn26">Leland B.
                                    Morris, Appointed Ambassador to Iran; Ambassador Morris
                                    presented his credentials on August 21, 1944.</note> is
                                requested to inform the Department as soon as he feels in a position
                                to do so, whether he would consider it advisable for the Department
                                to request Dr. Millspaugh to come to Washington to give the
                                Department the benefit of his views regarding the American adviser
                                program in Iran.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Stettinius</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>